comments: Miller is very personable and a great clinical instructor, but her lectures are absolutely pointless. If she didn\'t take roll, I would never attend.
Her Psych class was not that card... just do your reading and you will be fine... she is very funny and friendly :)

As a clinical instructor, I think she is absolutely awesome. It\'s clear that she is at home in the psychiatric setting...and she can teach quite a bit from that perspective. However, her classroom skills are limited. She is disorganized and uses a test-bank for her exams. Reading ATI and the text will serve you well...

Pro: fun presenter; great personality; entertaining. Con: unorganized, procrastinates, unclear, there\'s no point of going to class bc there\'s nothing on the test base on lecture! blackboard quizzes are lame =cant view mistakes when submit the test,timer is less that one minute per question,gives option to fight incorrect answer but dont see result
